As part of my process of improvement and responsibility to make these sessions accurate and valuable, I listen to them all and will always correct errors made if any

Begin by clarifying a mistake I made last session

I said that Jesus was a common name, coming from the hebrew name Joseph but Jesus is actually Hebrew for Joshua which means "Yahweh saves"

Yahweh is the Hebrew name for God revealed to Moses at the burning bush in the book of Exodus in the old testament

Something I didn't mention but seems importnt is the meaning of Christ. It's not Jesus' last name

Christ derives from the Greek word Christos meaning anointed one. Translates to messiah in Hebrew meaning "the one who is anointed"

Christ points back to David as the anointed king of Israel and to the promise of an "anointed one", the messiah who would rule God's people

Last week we began our exploration of the gospel of Matthew

Levi was a Jewish tax collector. One day Jesus rocks up and calls Levi to follow him. Levi left his position as a tax collector and became Matthew

Matthew begins with the geneaology of Jesus Christ to demonstrate his legitimacy as the son of David and the son of Abraham

Matthew wrote this gospel for Jews so beginning with legitimizing Jesus by explicitly stating his lineage is important for credibility

Matthew explains the birth of Jesus to Joseph and Mary. Jesus was conceived within Mary by the Holy Spirit

Conception by the Holy Spirit instead of his human father (Joseph), allowed Jesus to be born without the inherent sinful nature inherited from Adam

This is an important point so i'll repeat it

The virgin birth of Jesus by Mary bypassed the inheritance of mans sinful nature inherited from Adam

The miraculour conception allowed Jesus to be fully human (through Mary) while remaining fully divine

Though this, Jesus effectively became a new covenant head to replace Adam

