-------> BEHAVIOUR (10min)

One of the core elements of our weekly fellowship service is a 10 minute discussion about bevaviours

What behaviours are expected of true Christians? What behaviours should be deleted if we aspire to live righteously

The bible offers us instruction for ther purpose of informing and shaping our actions

The goal isn't just to know Gods word, it's to apply the word in everyday life.

This weeks behaviour is prayer

Why should we pray?
What is prayer?
How should we pray?


--> WHY should we pray? 

What did Jesus say about prayer?

In the Bible, Jesus says to pray in private

Jesus says to avoid empty phrases. No mindless repetition Keep it simple and to the point. God knows what you need. Dont waste his time with fancy words. Make it simple and sincere

He offers us a template of how to pray

Forgiveness is a big part of prayer. Asking God to forgive our sins and forgiving others for their sins against us




-->WHAT is prayer?

A petition to God

A request to the trinity that is God the heavenly father, Jesus Christ Lord of Lords, and the Holy Spirit




--> HOW should we pray?



In Matthew chapter 6, Jesus gives very clear and explicit instruction about prayer

Chapter 6 verse 6: "but when you pray, go into your room and shut the door and pray to your Father who is in secret. Anyour Father who sees in secret will reward you"

Jesus continues in verse 7 saying: "and when you pray, do not heap up empty phrases as the gentiles do, for they think that they will be heard for their many words.

The he says, very clearly in verse 9, "pray like this"

He writes the Lord's prayer which many recite word for word but notice Jesus didn't say "Say this prayer", he said "pray like this"

So he's giving us a template for prayer which consists of an invocation and 6 petitions

--> Invocation: "Our Father in heaven" An invocation is the act of calling upon God. An opening sentence that serves as a request for God's attention 

--> Petition 1: "Hallowed be your name" Petition just means an earnest request made to a higher authority. This first petition is that God's name would be hallowed

Hallowed meaning treated with the highest honour and set apart as holy

--> Petition 2: "Your Kingdom come" The second petition is for the continual advancement of God's kingdom on earth

The presence of God's kingdom in the time after Jesus refers to the reign of Christ in the hearts and lives of believers and to the presence of Christ in his body, the church

True Christians. Genuine believers are called to constantly and increasingly reflect Christ's love, obey his laws, honour him, and proclaim the good news of the kingdom

--> Petitian 3: "your will be done" speaks of God's will

This petition asks that God's followers would behave in ways that are pleassing to him. 

Believers on earth are called to follow God in the same way he is obeyed in heaven

--> Petition 4: "Give us this day our daily bread"

A petition that our daily needs would be met

--> Petition 5: Forgiveness of our sins

A petition for the restoation of personal fellowship with God following sin. Asking to reconcile with God when we miss the mark

--> Petition 6: "Lead us not into temptation, deliver us from evil"

A petition to be spared circumstances that would tempt us to sin and a request to be protected from the evil enemy


That's how Jesus told us that we are to pray
- Invocation
- Praise for God's holiness
- The advancement of God's kingdom on earth
- God's will
- Ask that our needs be met
- Ask for forgiveness
- Ask for protection from evil


