-------> STEWARDSHIP (10 min)

In every fellowship gathering we will be spending 10 minutes discussing stewardship as it relates to time, money and health

Stewardship describes the job of taking care of something valuable that we have been entrusted with



Within a Christian context, stewardship describes the responsibility that we have as Christians to maintain and wisely use the gifts that God has given us

Todays stewardship topic relates to health, and specifically, what God's word says about the food we eat


In Genesis 9:3 God says "Every moving thing that lives shall be food for you. And as I gave you the green plants, I give you everything"

God is telling us that he gave us animals for food, the one caveat is to not consume the blood. The blood remains sacred and is not to be consumed


In Levicitus chapter 11 God tells Moses and Aaron to avoid eating camel, rock badger, hare or pig

Avoid anything in the water that does not have fins and scales

Avoid eating eagle, bearded vulture, black vulture, kite, falcon of any kind, ostrich, nighthawk, sea gull, hawk of any kind, little owl, cormorant, short eared owl, barn owl, tawny owl, carrion vulture, stork, herron, 
hoopoe and bat

Avoid winged insects on all fours except for locusts, cricket or grasshopper

Also avoid the mole rat, mouse, great lizards, geckos, monitor, lizard, sand lizard and chameleon

Avoid anything that swarms on the ground, whatever goes on its belly, what goes on all fours or whatever has many feet

He tells us superspecifcally what living creatures we should and shoudn't eat


Proverbs 23:20 says to be not among drunkards or aqmong gluttonous eaters of meat


1 Timothy 4:4 Paul reinforces the importance of thanksgiving and also says everything created by God is good. 

My interpretation of that is that natural food is good. God didnt create fruit roll ups so they probebably arent good for us. He did create meat, papaya, and dates, all of which are delicious and good for us











